{"type":"message","id":"89816148","parentId":"4903d166","timestamp":"2026-05-20T03:57:09.576Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to read TAPD cookies from Chrome where 周以天 (Bing Wang) is logged in. Let me think about how to do this.\n\nChrome cookies are stored in a SQLite database file. I need to:\n1. Find Chrome's profile path\n2. Access the Cookies database\n3. Extract cookies related to tapd.cn for 周以天's session\n\nBut wait - Chrome's cookie database is encrypted on Windows (using DPAPI). However, there's a simpler approach: I can use Playwright to launch Chrome with `--remote-debugging-port` or use the user data directory, or I could try reading the Chrome cookies directly.\n\nActually, the simplest approach is probably:\n1. Close all Chrome instances (since cookies file is locked when Chrome is running)\n   - Wait, the user said \"已关闭chrome\" earlier, so Chrome might already be closed\n2. Read the Chrome Cookies SQLite database\n\nBut the cookies are encrypted. Let me think...\n\nActually, there's a simpler approach. I can use Playwright to launch Chrome with the user's existing profile and then extract cookies from the page. Or I could use a tool to decrypt Chrome cookies.\n\nLet me first check if Chrome is still running, and then try to use Playwright to launch with a specific user data directory.\n\nWait, actually the simplest approach would be to use Playwright's `chromium.launchPersistentContext` with the user's Chrome profile, navigate to TAPD, and extract cookies.\n\nBut the user said \"已关闭chrome\" earlier, meaning Chrome was closed. But now they're saying to read the cookie from Chrome where 周以天 is logged in. Let me think about what profile this would be.\n\nActually, the Chrome window that was open earlier was probably my script's headed Playwright browser showing the TAPD login page (微信扫码). If 周以天 was using his own Chrome, I'd need to find his Chrome profile or user data directory.\n\nHmm, but actually the most likely scenario is: the user manually opened Chrome, logged into TAPD as 周以天, and now wants me to extract those cookies so the bug submission can use 周以天's cookies instead of 叶枝君's.\n\nLet me think about the practical approach:\n\n1. First find Chrome's user data directory (typically `C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data`)\n2. Then use Playwright to launch with that profile and extract cookies\n3. Or directly read the Cookies file (but they're encrypted)\n\nThe simplest approach: use Playwright with `launchPersistentContext` pointing to the Chrome user data directory, open TAPD, read cookies, save them.\n\nBut wait - if I launch Chrome with an existing profile, I might need to close Chrome first (cookies file lock). The user already said they closed Chrome earlier.\n\nLet me try a practical approach - use Playwright to launch with the local Chrome profile and extract cookies for tapd.cn.\n\nActually, even simpler: I can just use `npx playwright` or a node script to launch Chrome with the existing profile and dump the cookies.\n\nLet me first check where Chrome's user data is on this machine.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"明白了，周以天刚才在 Chrome 里登录了 TAPD，我去把他的 cookie 扒出来。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_3BdMFmgtq1rBZ05umfQ20791","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data\" -Directory | Select-Object Name"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":21576,"output":773,"cacheRead":7040,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29389,"cost":{"input":0.0030206400000000002,"output":0.00021644,"cacheRead":0.00019711999999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0034342}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779249417048,"responseId":"07e51170-be76-4116-b2db-1417f3fb1bd6"}}
