{"type":"message","id":"23e5e647","parentId":"96f042cd","timestamp":"2026-05-20T04:02:42.350Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, I just realized something important. Every time I kill Chrome and restart, the Chrome profile is NOT modified (unless Chrome writes to it during operation). The key cookies that 周以天 created are in the Chrome profile's cookies database. The issue with my v4 script might be that the cookies were already extracted by the first run (extract_tapd_cookies_copy.mjs) which successfully got the tapdsession.\n\nThe question is: why didn't the v4 script find more cookies like `t_u`, `t_cloud_login`? These cookies might not exist in the Chrome profile, or they might be stored differently.\n\nWait, actually, looking at the first successful run more carefully - it only found 5 cookies, and the key ones like `t_u`, `t_cloud_login`, `_t_crop`, `_t_uid` were missing. This could mean:\n\n1. The Chrome profile never had these cookies (they were created/modified by the Playwright session)\n2. These cookies are set via JavaScript and are host-only (not domain cookies)\n3. They have different domain configuration\n\nActually, from the TAPD keepalive documentation: the cookies are `tapdsession`, `t_u`, `t_cloud_login`, `_t_crop`, `_t_uid`. The `tapdsession` is the most critical one - it's the session cookie. The others might be tracking/user identification cookies.\n\nLet me check: were the previous cookies (from 叶枝君's login) that worked for TAPD automation more comprehensive? The previous tapd_cookies.json (before I overwrote it) had more cookies because the previous TAPD automation worked. Let me check the v4 script that should dump ALL cookies.\n\nActually, let me just run v4 and see what we get.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_cFnyW8Yd5m3QKrkoSteb0433","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace; node scripts/extract_tapd_cookies_v4.mjs","timeout":60}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":99,"output":469,"cacheRead":47872,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48440,"cost":{"input":0.000013860000000000001,"output":0.00013132,"cacheRead":0.0013404159999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0014855959999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779249754285,"responseId":"0ac9cb5d-a39b-4ca3-8183-5ca7d5e029b6"}}
{"type":"message","id":"2b4ce834","parentId":"23e5e647","timestamp":"2026-05-20T04:02:48.194Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_cFnyW8Yd5m3QKrkoSteb0433","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Total cookies in context: 0\nDomains: \n\nRelevant cookies: 0\n\n--- Navigating to TAPD ---\nURL: https://www.tapd.cn/cloud_logins/login?site=TAPD&ref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tapd.cn%2F31253609%2Fbugtrace%2Fbugs%2Fadd\n❌ Login required"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":5827,"aggregated":"Total cookies in context: 0\nDomains: \n\nRelevant cookies: 0\n\n--- Navigating to TAPD ---\nURL: https://www.tapd.cn/cloud_logins/login?site=TAPD&ref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tapd.cn%2F31253609%2Fbugtrace%2Fbugs%2Fadd\n❌ Login required","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779249768194}}
{"type":"message","id":"5476df44","parentId":"2b4ce834","timestamp":"2026-05-20T04:03:04.202Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"0 cookies! Something is wrong. The copied profile doesn't have any cookies. This means the cookies database wasn't properly copied, or Chrome encrypted cookies with a key that doesn't transfer when using Playwright.\n\nWait - on Windows, Chrome encrypts cookies using DPAPI (Data Protection API). The encryption key is stored in `Local State` file, but it's ALSO DPAPI-encrypted. When Playwright launches Chromium with a copied profile directory, it can still decrypt the cookies because DPAPI keys are machine-level and user-level (the same Windows user can decrypt).\n\nBut 0 cookies means the cookie database wasn't read at all. Maybe the Copy-Item didn't copy the `Network\\Cookies` file properly, or Playwright's Chromium can't read Chrome's cookie database format.\n\nActually, the issue might be that Chrome stores cookies in a SQLite database at `Default/Network/Cookies` (newer Chrome) or `Default/Cookies` (older). Since this is Chrome (not Chromium), and Playwright might use its own bundled Chromium (not system Chrome), the cookie format might differ.\n\nActually wait, `launchPersistentContext` creates a new context, not Chrome, and the cookies are managed by Playwright/Chromium in its own format. When using `launchPersistentContext(TEMP_PROFILE)`, Playwright creates a new browser context in that directory, but it doesn't automatically import Chrome's cookies from that directory. The user data directory structure and cookie storage are at the Chromium/Chrome level, not easily transferred.\n\nOK so now I understand the fundamental issue: \n- `launchPersistentContext` with an existing Chrome profile directory doesn't import Chrome's cookies into Playwright's context\n- The cookies need to be read separately from Chrome's encrypted cookie database\n\nThe first successful extraction (extract_tapd_cookies_copy.mjs) somehow got the cookies. Let me re-read that output... It got 5 cookies including tapdsession. How?\n\nActually, I think what happened was:\n1. The first run of the old script (extract_tapd_cookies_copy.mjs) navigated to TAPD\n2. Chrome was launched by Playwright with the copied profile\n3. Chrome read the cookies from its own database internally\n4. The page navigated to TAPD, and the cookies worked (because Chrome's rendering engine could decrypt them)\n5. The page was redirected to login (or not - the first one said it found tapdsession)\n6. The script called `context.cookies()` which reads the cookies managed by Playwright's context, not Chrome's internal cookies\n\nWait, but the first script DID find cookies. Let me re-check: it said \"Found 5 TAPD cookies\" and \"✅ tapdsession found\". How?\n\nActually, I think the distinction is:\n- `chromium.launchPersistentContext()` launches Chrome with a user data directory\n- Chrome reads the cookies from its SQLite database\n- `context.cookies()` returns the cookies that Playwright/Chrome currently has for the browsing context\n- When Chrome navigates to a page, Chrome's internal cookie jar (from the database) is used for HTTP requests\n- Playwright's `context.cookies()` API can access Chrome's cookie jar\n\nSo the first run ACTUALLY worked - Chrome loaded the profile, read the cookies, and Playwright could access them via `context.cookies()`.\n\nThe second and subsequent runs failed because... hmm, why? Maybe:\n1. The profile was corrupted by the first Playwright launch\n2. The copy included stale lock files\n3. Something changed between runs\n\nActually, let me reconsider. The first run with the OLD script (extract_tapd_cookies_copy.mjs) succeeded and got 5 cookies including tapdsession. But the v4 script (fresh copy) got 0 cookies. This suggests the copy process might not be working correctly, or the database wasn't fully copied.\n\nLet me check: does the copy include the `Network\\Cookies` file?","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_fVC9lj8H4rX6vHxfLa0e4047","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Test-Path \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data\\Default\\Network\\Cookies\"; Test-Path \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data\\Default\\Cookies\"; Test-Path \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\temp_chrome_profile\\Default\\Network\\Cookies\"; Test-Path \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\temp_chrome_profile\\Default\\Cookies\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":155,"output":1017,"cacheRead":48384,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":49556,"cost":{"input":0.000021700000000000002,"output":0.00028476,"cacheRead":0.0013547519999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0016612119999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779249768195,"responseId":"3090a57d-944a-48a0-bab2-1c91ef72058c"}}
