{"type":"message","id":"e73d9e76","parentId":"90706ea4","timestamp":"2026-05-20T04:03:29.908Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to also make sure it stays quiet. The issue with the previous runs might have been that when Playwright launched Chrome with the temp profile, Chrome wrote new data to it, including overwriting the cookie database. Let me modify the v4 script to NOT navigate first, just read the cookies immediately via a different approach.\n\nActually wait - there's still the fundamental issue that Playwright might overwrite the cookies database when it starts. Let me check: when `launchPersistentContext` starts with an existing user data directory, does it keep the existing cookies, or does it create a new browser context?\n\nActually, I think the issue is that `launchPersistentContext` creates a Chromium profile (not Chrome), and even though the directory path points to Chrome's profile, Playwright/Chromium won't be able to read Chrome's encrypted cookies database because:\n1. Chrome stores cookies in a SQLite database encrypted with a key stored in Local State (AES-256-GCM)\n2. The key itself is encrypted with Windows DPAPI\n3. Playwright's Chromium (or even system Chrome via Playwright) uses a different mechanism to manage cookies\n\nWhen `context.cookies()` is called, Playwright gets cookies from Chromium's in-memory cookie jar, not by reading the SQLite database. The cookies only get loaded into memory when Chromium starts up and reads the database.\n\nThe first run (extract_tapd_cookies_copy.mjs) DID find cookies, which means it works. The later runs failed because... let me think...\n\nAh! I bet the issue is that the first run's `finally` block deleted the temp profile BEFORE Chrome could properly close, causing Chrome to save an empty cookie database. Then when I re-copied, the re-copy might have happened during a time when Chrome processes were still writing.\n\nLet me try again with a truly fresh copy, and don't navigate to TAPD first - just read cookies immediately.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_UiF5lfsYuv2HJlxh2Pyh9518","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"/**\n * v5 - 不导航，直接读 profile 的 cookie，然后导航验证\n */\nimport { chromium } from 'playwright';\nimport fs from 'fs';\nimport path from 'path';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'url';\n\nconst __dirname = path.dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));\nconst WS_DIR = path.resolve(__dirname, '..');\nconst COOKIES_FILE = path.join(WS_DIR, 'tapd_cookies.json');\nconst TEMP_PROFILE = path.join(WS_DIR, 'temp_chrome_profile');\n\nasync function main() {\n  const context = await chromium.launchPersistentContext(TEMP_PROFILE, {\n    headless: false,\n    args: ['--no-sandbox'],\n  });\n\n  // 不创建新页面，直接用 context.cookies() 读取\n  // 这会从 Chromium 启动时加载的 SQLite 数据库中读取\n  const allCookies = await context.cookies();\n  console.log(`[INIT] Total cookies in context: ${allCookies.length}`);\n\n  if (allCookies.length > 0) {\n    const domains = [...new Set(allCookies.map(c => c.domain))].sort();\n    console.log('Domains:', domains.join(', '));\n    \n    const tapdRelated = allCookies.filter(c => {\n      const d = c.domain.toLowerCase();\n      const n = c.name.toLowerCase();\n      return d.includes('tapd') || d.includes('qq.com') || d.includes('tencent') ||\n             n.includes('tapd') || n.startsWith('t_') || n.startsWith('_t');\n    });\n    console.log(`\\nTAPD-related: ${tapdRelated.length}`);\n    tapdRelated.forEach(c => console.log(`  ${c.name} (${c.domain}): ${c.value.substring(0, 40)}`));\n\n    // 导航验证\n    const page = context.pages()[0] || await context.newPage();\n    console.log('\\n--- Navigating to validate ---');\n    await page.goto('https://www.tapd.cn/31253609/bugtrace/bugs/add', {\n      waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded',\n      timeout: 30000,\n    });\n    console.log('URL:', page.url());\n\n    if (page.url().includes('login')) {\n      console.log('❌ Login required');\n    } else {\n      console.log('✅ Auto-login OK');\n      const finalCookies = await context.cookies();\n      const finalTapd = finalCookies.filter(c => c.domain.includes('tapd.cn'));\n      console.log(`TAPD cookies after nav: ${finalTapd.length}`);\n      fs.writeFileSync(COOKIES_FILE, JSON.stringify(finalTapd, null, 2), 'utf8');\n      finalTapd.forEach(c => console.log(`  ${c.name}: ${c.value.substring(0, 40)}`));\n    }\n  } else {\n    console.log('❌ No cookies in profile at all!');\n  }\n\n  await context.close();\n  try { fs.rmSync(TEMP_PROFILE, { recursive: true, force: true }); } catch {}\n}\n\nmain().catch(err => {\n  console.error('FAILED:', err.message);\n  process.exit(1);\n});\n","path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\extract_tapd_cookies_v5.mjs"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":33,"output":1185,"cacheRead":50688,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51906,"cost":{"input":0.000004620000000000001,"output":0.00033180000000000004,"cacheRead":0.001419264,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001755684}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779249795605,"responseId":"fc32c86e-32c3-4549-a7b8-7275c4054a2f"}}
