{"type":"message","id":"4a9e30b4","parentId":"0ed91f1b","timestamp":"2026-05-20T04:03:44.922Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still 0 cookies. The issue is clear now: Playwright's `launchPersistentContext` with Chromium cannot read Chrome's encrypted cookie database. Chrome encrypts cookies with a key that is stored in `Local State` and encrypted with Windows DPAPI. When Chromium (Playwright's bundled browser) starts with this profile directory:\n\n1. It sees the SQLite cookies database\n2. Tries to decrypt using the key from Local State\n3. The key is DPAPI-encrypted, and Chromium might not be able to decrypt it (different encryption scheme)\n\nWait, actually, Chromium and Chrome use the same encryption format. But the issue might be that Chromium tries to read the database but fails silently because the database format has changed, or there's a schema mismatch.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. Looking at the first successful run again... The first run (extract_tapd_cookies_copy.mjs) used the SAME approach (launchPersistentContext) and it DID find 5 cookies including tapdsession. So it can work.\n\nWhat changed? Let me compare the copies:\n- First time: I copied the entire Default directory with `Copy-Item ... -Recurse -Force`\n- This time: I only copied Local State + Network\\Cookies + Network\\Cookies-journal\n\nMaybe Chrome needs more files from the Default directory to properly initialize and read the cookie store. Like maybe the `Bookmarks`, `Preferences`, or other config files are needed.\n\nLet me try the full copy again, but with robocopy for reliability.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_ooQLGQBUs8PY0gWs2WIY9835","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$tmpProfile = \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\temp_chrome_profile\"; if (Test-Path $tmpProfile) { Remove-Item -Recurse -Force $tmpProfile }; New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $tmpProfile -Force | Out-Null; Copy-Item \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data\\Local State\" -Destination \"$tmpProfile\\Local State\" -Force; robocopy \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data\\Default\" \"$tmpProfile\\Default\" /E /R:2 /W:2 /NFL /NDL /NP 2>&1 | Out-String; Write-Host \"=== Cookies file ===\"; Test-Path \"$tmpProfile\\Default\\Network\\Cookies\"; Get-Item \"$tmpProfile\\Default\\Network\\Cookies\" | Select-Object Length; Write-Host \"=== Full copy done ===\"","timeout":120}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":110,"output":608,"cacheRead":52352,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53070,"cost":{"input":0.0000154,"output":0.00017024000000000002,"cacheRead":0.001465856,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001651496}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779249817418,"responseId":"ee6f1299-5a33-48d0-9bd2-9ee195117f17"}}
