{"type":"message","id":"b07f633a","parentId":"0602137c","timestamp":"2026-05-20T04:06:27.614Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The script started but got stuck after \"loaded assembly\". The `FromBase64String` might be failing or hanging. Actually, the output just stopped, which means the script crashed or is still running. The base64 string contains invalid characters or the `ProtectedData.Unprotect` is throwing an exception that's not caught properly.\n\nLet me check... The base64 data I used for the PowerShell script was hard-coded. But there might be some character that's being escaped or lost. Let me try a much simpler approach - save the encrypted key as a binary file and have PowerShell read it from a file.\n\nActually, let me try yet another approach. Let me use Python via the `activestate` or use `npx` to use a simpler tool. Or let me try using a .NET C# script.\n\nWait, actually there's a much simpler way. Let me use `edge-powershell` or just run PowerShell through cmd. But the fundamental issue is that the base64 string is being modified somehow in the PowerShell execution.\n\nLet me take a step back and think about this differently. Instead of trying to manually decrypt cookies, I can:\n\n1. Write a tiny C# program that decrypts the Chrome cookies\n2. Compile and run it\n3. Or use a more creative approach\n\nActually, `csc.exe` (C# compiler) is available on Windows. Let me write a small C# program.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_NhKUJO6DAi8GpY9e9gBd1648","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"using System;\nusing System.IO;\nusing System.Security.Cryptography;\nusing System.Text;\n\nclass DecryptChromeKey\n{\n    static void Main()\n    {\n        string localStatePath = @\"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data\\Local State\";\n        string cookiesDbPath = @\"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data\\Default\\Network\\Cookies\";\n        string outputFile = @\"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\tapd_cookies.json\";\n        \n        // Read Local State\n        string json = File.ReadAllText(localStatePath);\n        // Simple JSON parsing to get encrypted_key\n        int keyStart = json.IndexOf(\"\\\"encrypted_key\\\"\") + \"\\\"encrypted_key\\\"\".Length;\n        keyStart = json.IndexOf('\"', keyStart) + 1;\n        int keyEnd = json.IndexOf('\"', keyStart);\n        string encryptedKeyB64 = json.Substring(keyStart, keyEnd - keyStart);\n        \n        // Decode and decrypt the key\n        byte[] raw = Convert.FromBase64String(encryptedKeyB64);\n        byte[] encryptedData = new byte[raw.Length - 5];\n        Array.Copy(raw, 5, encryptedData, 0, encryptedData.Length);\n        \n        byte[] aesKey = ProtectedData.Unprotect(encryptedData, null, DataProtectionScope.CurrentUser);\n        Console.WriteLine(\"AES Key hex: \" + BitConverter.ToString(aesKey).Replace(\"-\", \"\").Substring(0, 20) + \"...\");\n        Console.WriteLine(\"AES Key length: \" + aesKey.Length);\n        \n        // Read cookie database\n        if (!File.Exists(cookiesDbPath))\n        {\n            Console.WriteLine(\"Cookie DB not found at: \" + cookiesDbPath);\n            return;\n        }\n        \n        // Use Microsoft.Data.Sqlite or System.Data.SQLite\n        // For simplicity, read the raw bytes and extract tapd cookies manually\n        Console.WriteLine(\"Cookie DB exists, size: \" + new FileInfo(cookiesDbPath).Length);\n        \n        // Write key for debugging\n        File.WriteAllText(Path.ChangeExtension(outputFile, \".key.b64.txt\"), Convert.ToBase64String(aesKey));\n        Console.WriteLine(\"Key saved to: \" + Path.ChangeExtension(outputFile, \".key.b64.txt\"));\n    }\n}\n","path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\decrypt_key.cs"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":21,"output"