{"type":"message","id":"8c1497a0","parentId":"50ac1167","timestamp":"2026-05-20T04:07:30.396Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good progress! PowerShell DPAPI decryption works and we got a 32-byte AES key. But the AES-GCM decryption fails with \"Unsupported state or unable to authenticate data\". This means either:\n1. The AES key is wrong\n2. The nonce/ciphertext/tag extraction is wrong\n3. The encryption scheme has changed\n\nThe key is 32 bytes (AES-256). The GCM authentication tag check failed, meaning either the key is wrong or the data boundaries are wrong.\n\nLet me debug more carefully by checking the data format. Maybe v20 uses a different layout. Let me check the Chrome source to see what v20 means.\n\nActually, looking at Chrome source code, the encrypted value format for newer Chrome versions is still:\n- version (3 bytes)\n- nonce (12 bytes) \n- ciphertext\n- tag (16 bytes)\n\nBut wait - the `v20` format might actually be `v20` + variations. Let me check if the tag is actually at the end.\n\nActually, I wonder if the issue is that the encrypted_value field for some cookies might be empty or null, and I'm trying to decrypt an empty buffer. Let me add proper validation.\n\nActually, looking at the error messages, 17 out of 17 cookies failed with \"Unsupported state or unable to authenticate data\". This means either:\n1. All encrypted values are valid but the key is wrong\n2. The data format parsing is wrong (wrong nonce/ciphertext/tag boundaries)\n\nLet me dump the actual bytes to verify the format.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"解密失败了（GCM 认证失败）。看看 v20 的具体数据格式："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_WT9ipIhwrq9UoXjtdG3I3079","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport fs from 'fs';\nimport crypto from 'crypto';\nimport { execSync } from 'child_process';\n\nconst COOKIES_DB = 'C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\Google\\\\Chrome\\\\User Data\\\\Default\\\\Network\\\\Cookies';\nconst LOCAL_STATE = 'C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\Google\\\\Chrome\\\\User Data\\\\Local State';\n\n// 获取 AES key（用之前已验证的方法）\nconst state = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(LOCAL_STATE, 'utf8'));\nconst raw = Buffer.from(state.os_crypt.encrypted_key, 'base64');\nconst encryptedKeyData = raw.slice(5);\n\nconst tempKeyFile = 'C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\temp_key.bin';\nconst tempOutFile = 'C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\temp_key_out.b64';\nfs.writeFileSync(tempKeyFile, encryptedKeyData);\n\nconst psScript = `Add-Type -AssemblyName System.Security; $data = [System.IO.File]::ReadAllBytes('${tempKeyFile.replace(/\\\\/g, '\\\\\\\\')}'); $key = [System.Security.Cryptography.ProtectedData]::Unprotect($data, $null, [System.Security.Cryptography.DataProtectionScope]::CurrentUser); [System.IO.File]::WriteAllText('${tempOutFile.replace(/\\\\/g, '\\\\\\\\')}', [Convert]::ToBase64String($key))`;\nfs.writeFileSync('C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\temp_ps.ps1', psScript);\nexecSync(`powershell -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File \"C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\temp_ps.ps1\"`, { encoding: 'utf8', timeout: 10000 });\n\nconst keyB64 = fs.readFileSync(tempOutFile, 'utf8').trim();\nconst aesKey = Buffer.from(keyB64, 'base64');\n\n// 清理临时文件\ntry { fs.unlinkSync(tempKeyFile); } catch {}\ntry { fs.unlinkSync(tempOutFile); } catch {}\ntry { fs.unlinkSync('C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\temp_ps.ps1'); } catch {}\n\nconsole.log('AES Key (32 bytes):', aesKey.toString('hex'));\nconsole.log('');\n\n// 读 tapdsession cookie 的加密数据，做详细分析\nconst db = new Database(COOKIES_DB, { readonly: true });\nconst rows = db.prepare(`SELECT host_key, name, value, encrypted_value FROM cookies WHERE host_key LIKE '%tapd%' AND name = 'tapdsession'`).all();\n\nif (rows.length > 0) {\n  const row = rows[0];\n  const buf = Buffer.isBuffer(row.encrypted_value) ? row.encrypted_value : Buffer.from(row.encrypted_value);\n  \n  console.log('=== tapdsession encrypted_value ===');\n  console.log('Length:', buf.length);\n  console.log('Full hex:', buf.toString('hex'));\n  console.log('Version:', buf.slice(0, 3).toString());\n  \n  // v20 格式：尝试多种解析\n  const version = buf.slice(0, 3).toString();\n  \n  // Method 1: 3-byte version + 12-byte nonce + ciphertext + 16-byte tag\n  const nonce1 = buf.slice(3, 15);\n  const ciphertext1 = buf.slice(15, -16);\n  const tag1 = buf.slice(-16);\n  \n  console.log('\\n--- Method 1 (v20 + 12B nonce + ciphertext + 16B tag) ---');\n  console.log('Nonce hex:', nonce1.toString('hex'), `(${nonce1.length} bytes)`);\n  console.log('Ciphertext length:', ciphertext1.length, 'bytes');\n  console.log('Tag hex:', tag1.toString('hex'), `(${tag1.length} bytes)`);\n  \n  // Try decrypt with method 1\n  try {\n    const decipher = crypto.createDecipheriv('aes-256-gcm', aesKey, nonce1);\n    decipher.setAuthTag(tag1);\n    const pt = Buffer.concat([decipher.update(ciphertext1), decipher.final()]);\n    console.log('Decrypted:', pt.toString());\n  } catch (e) {\n    console.log('Method 1 FAILED:', e.message.substring(0, 80));\n  }\n  \n  // Method 2: Maybe the format is different - try with nonce shifted\n  // Some versions might use a different nonce length (e.g., 16 bytes)\n  // Or the tag might be stored differently\n  \n  // Try all possible nonce starting positions (0-20)\n  for (let nonceLen = 8; nonceLen <= 16; nonceLen++) {\n    for (let start = 3; start < Math.min(20, buf.length - nonceLen - 16); start++) {\n      const nonce = buf.slice(start, start + nonceLen);\n      const remaining = buf.slice(start + nonceLen);\n      if (remaining.length <= 16) continue;\n      \n      const ciphertext = remaining.slice(0, -16);\n      const tag = remaining.slice(-16);\n      \n      try {\n        const decipher = crypto.createDecipheriv('aes-256-gcm', aesKey, nonce);\n        decipher.setAuthTag(tag);\n        const pt = Buffer.concat([decipher.update(ciphertext), decipher.final()]);\n        console.log(`\\n✅ Method: version=${version}, nonceStart=${start}, nonceLen=${nonceLen}`);\n        console.log('  Nonce:', nonce.toString('hex'));\n        console.log('  Decrypted:', pt.toString('utf8'));\n        break;\n      } catch(e) {\n        // ignore\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  \n  // Method 3: Maybe the key derivation is different for v20\n  // Try without version prefix\n  for (let nonceLen = 8; nonceLen <= 16; nonceLen++) {\n    for (let start = 3; start < Math.min(20, buf.length - nonceLen - 16 + 1); start++) {\n      const nonce = buf.slice(start, start + nonceLen);\n      const remaining = buf.slice(start + nonceLen);\n      if (remaining.length <= 16) continue;\n      \n      const ciphertext = remaining.slice(0, -16);\n      const tag = remaining.slice(-16);\n      \n      // v20 might use a different key derivation!\n      // Try with SHA-256 of the key\n      const derivedKey = crypto.createHash('sha256').update(aesKey).digest();\n      try {\n        const decipher = crypto.createDecipheriv('aes-256-gcm', derivedKey, nonce);\n        decipher.setAuthTag(tag);\n        const pt = Buffer.concat([decipher.update(ciphertext), decipher.final()]);\n        console.log(`\\n✅ Method (SHA256 key): nonceStart=${start}, nonceLen=${nonceLen}`);\n        console.log('  Decrypted:', pt.toString('utf8'));\n        break;\n      } catch(e) {}\n    }\n  }\n  \n} else {\n  console.log('No tapdsession cookie found');\n}\n\ndb.close();\n","path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\debug_v20_format.mjs"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":675,"output":2046,"cacheRead":74624,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77345,"cost":{"input":0.0000945,"output":0.00057288,"cacheRead":0.0020894719999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0027568519999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779250033213,"res