{"type":"message","id":"07d2cab9","parentId":"ae482f52","timestamp":"2026-05-20T04:10:09.318Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Port 9222 is not listening despite Chrome running with `--remote-debugging-port=9222`. This is strange. Maybe Chrome is trying to bind to an IPv6 address, or the port is being used by something else.\n\nLet me check: when I ran the temp_cp Chrome earlier, port 9222 was listening. But now with the default profile, it's not. Maybe Chrome on Windows with recent versions doesn't enable the debugging port on the default profile as a security measure.\n\nLet me try a different port number.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_3uwB0QFlPIGK2l6hAc5I3430","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Process chrome | Stop-Process -Force; Start-Sleep -Seconds 2; Remove-Item -Force \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data\\SingletonLock\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue; Start-Sleep -Seconds 2; Start-Process -FilePath \"C:\\Program Files\\Google\\Chrome\\Application\\chrome.exe\" -ArgumentList \"--remote-debugging-port=9333\" -WindowStyle Normal; Start-Sleep -Seconds 6; netstat -an | findstr \":9333\" 2>&1","timeout":20}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":105,"output":295,"cacheRead":87040,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87440,"cost":{"input":0.000014700000000000002,"output":0.0000826,"cacheRead":0.00243712,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00253442}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779250205002,"responseId":"36adb8b9-d78a-46c7-84db-f2a456fb90ae"}}
