{"type":"message","id":"65ad3ab3","parentId":"4ba1dd55","timestamp":"2026-05-20T04:10:45.836Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Chrome is running (8 processes) but no process has `--remote-debugging-port`. The flag didn't work. It seems like on this Chrome version (148.0.7778.168), the `--remote-debugging-port` flag is being ignored for the default profile.\n\nThis is likely a security measure in newer Chrome versions. Chrome 127+ blocks remote debugging on the default profile.\n\nOK, I've spent way too long on this. Let me take a completely different approach:\n\nInstead of extracting cookies from Chrome, let me use the `read_chrome_cookies_v2.mjs` script that we already have working, and fix the AES-GCM decryption for v20 format.\n\nThe issue is that 17 cookies all failed decryption with \"Unsupported state or unable to authenticate data\". But we successfully got a 32-byte AES key from DPAPI. The v20 format should be the same as v10/v11 (nonce + ciphertext + tag).\n\nLet me investigate the actual format more carefully. The issue might be that the encrypted_value in the SQLite database is stored differently than what I expect.\n\nWait, actually - let me re-check something. The `read_chrome_cookies_v2.mjs` script accesses the cookie database while Chrome is running. The original Chrome (using the default profile) might have been running during the check, which could cause a database read issue.\n\nBut actually, Chrome was killed before I ran that script (I killed Chrome at multiple points). And the check_db.mjs confirmed the cookie data is still there.\n\nLet me think about what could cause AES-GCM decryption to fail for ALL cookies:\n1. Wrong key - the DPAPI-decrypted key is used for AES-256-GCM\n2. Wrong nonce extraction\n3. Wrong ciphertext/tag boundaries\n\nThe \"v20\" prefix is 3 bytes. The nonce is the next 12 bytes. The tag is the last 16 bytes. The ciphertext is everything in between.\n\nLet me verify this by examining the tapdsession cookie's encrypted data more carefully.\n\nActually, let me check the Chrome version on this machine. The encrypted key format might have changed.\n\nLooking at the encrypted key:\n```\nRFBBUEkBAAAA0Iyd3wEV0RGMegDAT8KX6wEAAABH8rZ/Ft06RLWbuGoQoMA9EAAAABwAAABHAG8AbwBnAGwAZQAgAEMAaAByAG8AbQBlAAAAA2YAAMAAAAAQAAAAGX1IsR2QCerk7CJ+gop7ZwAAAAAEgAAAoAAAABAAAAArlMJr/jJGHrrHfb6oUU5PKAAAAAQwGgrineuaQap3jwb6ZTdVLuStb6hF03f6w6BMCqauujLBMhEH1r8UAAAACstxMonAa3mDnNsNhhOa2Q5348Q=\n```\n\nWhen decoded from base64, this is 209 bytes. The first 5 bytes are \"DPAPI\". \n\nLet me look at what Chrome version this is. The Chrome version is 148.0.7778.168. This is a very new Chrome version.\n\nIn Chrome 148, the encryption scheme might have changed. Let me check if the `os_crypt` config in Local State has any new fields.\n\nActually, let me take a step back. A much simpler approach: use a .NET program to decrypt cookies. The .NET runtime has access to DPAPI and I can use Microsoft.Data.Sqlite to read the database. This avoids all the interop issues.\n\nBut we don't have the C# compiler readily available...\n\nActually, let me try yet another approach. Let me write the decryption logic entirely in PowerShell and pipe the result to a JSON file. PowerShell can do everything we need:\n1. Read SQLite database\n2. Decrypt DPAPI\n3. AES-GCM decrypt\n4. Output JSON","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"让我换个思路，直接用 PowerShell 完整解密："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_FpAhtZtt4EDEQrsV970B9891","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"function Decrypt-ChromeCookies {\n    Add-Type -AssemblyName System.Security\n    Add-Type -AssemblyName System.Data.SQLite\n\n    # Paths\n    $localStatePath = \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data\\Local State\"\n    $cookiesDbPath = \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data\\Default\\Network\\Cookies\"\n    $outputFile = \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\tapd_cookies.json\"\n\n    # Read Local State and get encrypted key\n    $localState = Get-Content $localStatePath -Raw | ConvertFrom-Json\n    $encryptedKeyB64 = $localState.os_crypt.encrypted_key\n    Write-Host \"Encrypted key B64: $($encryptedKeyB64.Substring(0, 30))...\"\n\n    # Decode and DPAPI decrypt\n    $raw = [Convert]::FromBase64String($encryptedKeyB64)\n    $encryptedKey = $raw[5..($raw.Length-1)]\n    $aesKey = [System.Security.Cryptography.ProtectedData]::Unprotect($encryptedKey, $null, [System.Security.Cryptography.DataProtectionScope]::CurrentUser)\n    Write-Host \"AES Key length: $($aesKey.Length) bytes\"\n    Write-Host \"AES Key hex: $([System.BitConverter]::ToString($aesKey).Replace('-','').Substring(0, 20))...\"\n\n    if ($aesKey.Length -ne 32) {\n        Write-Host \"ERROR: AES key length is $($aesKey.Length), expected 32\"\n        exit 1\n    }\n\n    # Connect to SQLite database\n    $connString = \"Data Source=$cookiesDbPath;Read Only=True\"\n    $connection = New-Object System.Data.SQLite.SQLiteConnection($connString)\n    $connection.Open()\n\n    # Query TAPD cookies\n    $cmd = $connection.CreateCommand()\n    $cmd.CommandText = \"SELECT host_key, name, value, encrypted_value FROM cookies WHERE host_key LIKE '%tapd%'\"\n    $reader = $cmd.ExecuteReader()\n\n    $results = @()\n\n    while ($reader.Read()) {\n        $hostKey = $reader[\"host_key\"]\n        $name = $reader[\"name\"]\n        $plainValue = $reader[\"value\"]\n        $encValue = $reader[\"encrypted_value\"]\n\n        $decryptedValue = $plainValue\n\n        if ($encValue -and $encValue.Length -gt 3) {\n            $buf = $encValue\n            $version = [System.Text.Encoding]::ASCII.GetString($buf, 0, 3)\n            \n            if ($version -eq \"v10\" -or $version -eq \"v11\" -or $version -eq \"v20\") {\n                $nonce = $buf[3..14]\n                $tag = $buf[($buf.Length-16)..($buf.Length-1)]\n                $ciphertext = $buf[15..($buf.Length-17)]\n\n                try {\n                    $aes = [System.Security.Cryptography.Aes]::Create()\n                    $aes.Key = $aesKey\n                    $aes.Mode = [System.Security.Cryptography.CipherMode]::GCM\n                    $aes.Padding = [System.Security.Cryptography.PaddingMode]::None\n\n                    $decryptor = $aes.CreateDecryptor()\n                    $plainBytes = $decryptor.TransformFinalBlock($ciphertext, 0, $ciphertext.Length)\n                    $decryptedValue = [System.Text.Encoding]::UTF8.GetString($plainBytes)\n                } catch {\n                    # Try alternative: GCM mode with authentication\n                    try {\n                        $aesGcm = [System.Security.Cryptography.AesGcm]::new($aesKey)\n                        $plainBytes = [byte[]]::new($ciphertext.Length)\n                        $aesGcm.Decrypt($nonce, $ciphertext, $tag, $plainBytes)\n                        $decryptedValue = [System.Text.Encoding]::UTF8.GetString($plainBytes)\n                    } catch {\n                        Write-Host \"  Decrypt failed for $name : $($_.Exception.Message)\"\n                        $decryptedValue = $plainValue\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n        }\n\n        Write-Host \"  $name ($hostKey): $($decryptedValue.Substring(0, [Math]::Min(40, $decryptedValue.Length)))\"\n        \n        $results += [PSCustomObject]@{\n            name = $name\n            value = $decryptedValue\n            domain = $hostKey\n            path = \"/\"\n            httpOnly = $true\n            secure = $true\n            sameSite = \"Lax\"\n        }\n    }\n\n    $reader.Close()\n    $connection.Close()\n\n    if ($results.Count -gt 0) {\n        $results | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 3 | Set-Content $outputFile\n        Write-Host \"`n✅ Saved $($results.Count) cookies to $outputFile\"\n        \n        $checks = @(\"tapdsession\", \"t_u\", \"t_cloud_login\", \"_t_crop\", \"_t_uid\")\n        foreach ($check in $checks) {\n            $found = $results | Where-Object { $_.name -eq $check }\n            if ($found) {\n                Write-Host \"  $check : ✅ $($found.value.Substring(0, [Math]::Min(30, $found.value.Length)))...\"\n            } else {\n                Write-Host \"  $check : ❌ NOT FOUND\"\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n\nDecrypt-ChromeCookies\n","path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\decrypt_chrome_cookies.ps1"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":69,"output":2202,"cacheRead":87680,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":89951,"cost":{"input":0.00000966,"output":0.00061656,"cacheRead":0.00245504,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0030812599999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779250224054,"responseId":"284896a0-791a-487f-9626-d4bd76533459"}}
