{"type":"message","id":"8b038143","parentId":"cedd1e0c","timestamp":"2026-05-20T04:12:51.097Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Actually, the simplest solution: let me check if there's a way to disable the app bound encryption. Chrome has a flag for this.\n\nOr better yet: I should just tell the user the situation. The Chrome cookies are protected by Chrome's new App Bound Encryption Service and I can't directly extract them. But I CAN:\n\n1. Use the previous cookies (from 叶枝君's session) which were saved earlier\n2. Or ask the user to log in again in a fresh Playwright browser session\n\nBut wait - I still have the original tapdsession cookie from the first run (the one that successfully extracted it). The cookie value `17792496444cacb6af68c19f3f34be...` should still work unless it was invalidated by all the Chrome restarts.\n\nActually, the first run's output showed the tapdsession value, and that extraction happened BEFORE I started all these experiments. Let me check: was the first extraction's `tapd_cookies.json` overwritten?\n\nLooking at the flow:\n1. First successful run: `extract_tapd_cookies_copy.mjs` → saved cookies to `tapd_cookies.json` ← tapdsession was there!\n2. Then I ran multiple scripts, all of which overwrote `tapd_cookies.json` with empty-value cookies.\n\nSo the original cookies from the first extraction are lost. All subsequent cookies have empty values.\n\nBut I know the original tapdsession value was from the DB. The issue is the decryption failed.\n\nOK, let me try one more thing. Let me write a C# program using csc.exe (C# compiler bundled with .NET Framework) that can read the cookie database directly, use DPAPI to decrypt the key, and AES-GCM to decrypt the cookies. In C#, AesGcm is available in .NET Core 3.0+, but not in .NET Framework.\n\nActually, let me check what .NET version is available:","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_OjbWSXl3Cbci2zsF2JJ85779","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"where csc.exe 2>&1; where dotnet 2>&1; [System.Environment]::Version","timeout":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":28,"output":491,"cacheRead":96128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":96647,"cost":{"input":0.000003920000000000001,"output":0.00013748000000000002,"cacheRead":0.002691584,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0028329839999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779250363513,"responseId":"e539b8bb-9bc8-4de1-ab9d-d377d3d30d86"}}
