{"type":"message","id":"9cb07192","parentId":"e3414f30","timestamp":"2026-05-20T04:14:18.954Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The current tapd_cookies.json has:\n1. tapdsession: `17792503160c843fcd5d91ae5d8ae9f4caa4e061212ac78e04bb82e2e088a35f2381c495b1` - this is a REAL value!\n2. app_locale_name: zh_CN\n3. sso-login-token: 33a88330...\n4. __root_domain_v: .tapd.cn\n5. _qddaz: QD.178878752070032\n6. _qdda: 3-1.1\n7. _qddab: 3-42aw89.mpdjp6ti\n\nBut I notice the important cookies `t_u`, `t_cloud_login`, `_t_crop`, `_t_uid` are MISSING! These are needed for the user identification.\n\nThe tapdsession expires at timestamp 1779855116.234807. Let me convert:\n1779855116 / (24*3600) = 20601 days from epoch 1601... that's `new Date((1779855116 - 11644473600)*1000)` = wait, the timestamp from Chrome cookies DB is in microseconds since 1601-01-01. But Playwright's `context.cookies()` already converts it to standard Unix timestamps (seconds since 1970).\n\n1779855116 seconds ≈ 2026-05-27 (expires in ~7 days). That's correct for a tapdsession!\n\nThe SSO login token has an earlier expiry (1779250916 ≈ very soon, within hours).\n\nSo we DO have a valid tapdsession! But missing the user identification cookies (t_u, t_cloud_login, etc.). The tapdsession alone might still work for authentication because it contains the session state server-side.\n\nBut I don't know what was the source of this file - was it from the first extraction (extract_tapd_cookies_copy.mjs) or the CDP connection? The expiry timestamp 1779855116 corresponds to approximately 2026-05-27, which is 7 days from now. This is consistent with the tapdsession that was created by 周以天's login.\n\nActually, I think this file comes from extract_via_cdp.mjs! That script connected to port 9222, navigated to TAPD, found it needed login, waited 30s, and during that time... hmm, but I killed it.\n\nOr wait - the extract_via_cdp_v2.mjs was the one that started Chrome via `start` command. Maybe it ran for a while and succeeded partially because I used a different script more recently.\n\nActually, let me check: the FIRST successful run (extract_tapd_cookies_copy.mjs) had tapdsession `17792496444cacb6a...` and the current file has `17792503160c843fcd5...`. These are DIFFERENT values. So the current file is NOT from the first run.\n\nThe v2 script (read_chrome_cookies_v2.mjs) saved 17 cookies with empty values, NOT this file.\n\nSo this file must be from one of the CDP scripts. The CDP script (extract_via_cdp.mjs) ran with the temp_cp Chrome on port 9222. It navigated to TAPD, got login page, waited 30s, and I killed it. During the 30s wait, the script is just waiting - it doesn't save cookies until after the wait.\n\nUnless... there was a script I forgot about, or there's an intermediate state where the CDP connection gave partial cookies.\n\nActually, I think I might have the order wrong. Let me reconsider:\n\nThe first extraction (extract_tapd_cookies_copy.mjs) succeeded and saved 5 cookies.\nThen `read_chrome_cookies.mjs` (first version) ran and saved ALL 17 cookies with the \"v20 unknown\" issue, but it had `finalValue = row.value` fallback, which might have some values.\n\nWait, looking at the first `read_chrome_cookies.mjs` output:\n```\n  tapdsession (.tapd.cn): \n```\nEmpty! So that script couldn't get the value.\n\nSo the current file with the real tapdsession must be from... let me check the CDP script flow. The CDP scripts connect to Chrome, and `context.cookies()` should return the cookies that Chrome has in memory. But if Chrome (temp_cp) showed login page, then Chrome doesn't have the cookies.\n\nOK actually this is getting circular. The important thing is: we HAVE a valid tapdsession in the cookie file. Let me just verify that this tapdsession works for TAPD automation by launching a quick login test.\n\nBut I'm missing `t_u`, `t_cloud_login`, `_t_crop`, `_t_uid`. These might be needed for proper user identification. Without them, TAPD might not recognize the user.\n\nLet me try to use the current cookies for a TAPD login test. If the tapdsession alone works, great. If not, I'll need the user to log in again.\n\nActually, I realize I should check: are these 7 cookies from the ORIGINAL tapd_cookies.json that existed BEFORE I started working? Let me check - was there a previous working tapd_cookies.json that had the full set of cookies?\n\nLooking at the MEMORY.md:\n```\n### 登录方式选择\n主人选了**微信扫码登录**，二维码页面已调通，扫一扫即可登录。\n登录后保存 Cookie，后续分析提单页面结构（bug/需求表单字段）。\n```\n\nAnd TAPD keepalive was working. So there was a previously working tapd_cookies.json with all cookies. But the user just asked me to get 周以天's cookies (from Chrome), which I then tried to extract and overwrite.\n\nSo the previous tapd_cookies.json (with 叶枝君's login) was overwritten during my experiments. And my attempts to get 周以天's cookies only partially succeeded (got tapdsession but missing many cookies).\n\nLet me try a quick test to see if the current cookies work for TAPD.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"看起来有一段有效的 `tapdsession` 已经被提取出来了！但还缺 `t_u`、`t_cloud_login` 等身份 cookie。让我快速测试一下能否用："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_m1BHsfUmG5hSt2sSta9W5845","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"/**\n * 快速测试当前 TAPD cookie 是否有效\n */\nimport { chromium } from 'playwright';\nimport fs from 'fs';\nimport path from 'path';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'url';\n\nconst __dirname = path.dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));\nconst WS_DIR = path.resolve(__dirname, '..');\nconst COOKIES_FILE = path.join(WS_DIR, 'tapd_cookies.json');\n\nasync function main() {\n  const cookies = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(COOKIES_FILE, 'utf8'));\n  console.log(`Testing ${cookies.length} cookies...`);\n  \n  const browser = await chromium.launch({ headless: false, args: ['--no-sandbox'] });\n  const context = await browser.newContext();\n  \n  // 添加存储的 cookie\n  // Playwright 的 addCookies 要求 cookies 有 url 或 domain+path\n  for (const c of cookies) {\n    try {\n      await context.addCookies([{\n        name: c.name,\n        value: c.value,\n        domain: c.domain,\n        path: c.path || '/',\n      }]);\n    } catch (e) {\n      console.warn(`  Failed to add ${c.name}: ${e.message}`);\n    }\n  }\n  \n  const page = await context.newPage();\n  console.log('Navigating to TAPD...');\n  await page.goto('https://www.tapd.cn/31253609/bugtrace/bugs/add', {\n    waitUntil: 'networkidle',\n    timeout: 30000,\n  });\n  console.log('URL:', page.url());\n  \n  if (page.url().includes('login')) {\n    console.log('❌ Session invalid - need to login');\n  } else {\n    console.log('✅ Session valid!');\n    // 获取当前登录的用户信息\n    const title = await page.title();\n    console.log('Page title:', title);\n    \n    // 保存完整 cookies\n    const finalCookies = await context.cookies();\n    const tapdCookies = finalCookies.filter(c => c.domain.includes('tapd.cn'));\n    console.log(`TAPD cookies after login: ${tapdCookies.length}`);\n    tapdCookies.forEach(c => console.log(`  ${c.name}: ${c.value.substring(0, 40)}`));\n    fs.writeFileSync(COOKIES_FILE, JSON.stringify(tapdCookies, null, 2), 'utf8');\n    console.log('✅ Updated cookie file');\n  }\n  \n  await browser.close();\n}\n\nmain().catch(err => {\n  console.error('FAILED:', err.message);\n  process.exit(1);\n});\n","path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\test_cookies.mjs"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":750,"output":2024,"cacheRead":102016,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":104790,"cost":{"input":0.000105,"output":0.00056672,"cacheRead":0.0028564479999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003528168}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779250434324,"responseId":"15e7d0bb-5538-4f4c-b814-6302d3d9f03a"}}
