{"type":"message","id":"74346bb8","parentId":"18959f1b","timestamp":"2026-05-20T06:09:01.179Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The netlog uses a special JSON format - it's NOT standard JSON lines. The file starts with `{\"constants\":{...}` then `\"events\": [` on line 1, and then each line is a JSON object followed by a comma. It's one big JSON object essentially.\n\nThe issue is each individual line IS valid JSON but there's the trailing comma that makes it invalid when parsed alone. Also, the first line is a constants definition.\n\nI need to parse the events array properly. The simplest way is to:\n1. Read the raw text\n2. Find all event objects between the `\"events\": [` and the end\n3. Strip trailing commas\n4. Parse as a JSON array\n\nOr I can use a streaming JSON parser. Let me write a simpler approach.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_0VvZwmX6HKOrMIZ3aj8a1146","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace; node -e \"\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst content = fs.readFileSync('chrome_netlog.json', 'utf8');\n\n// Find events array - between 'events\\\": [' and end\nconst start = content.indexOf('\\\"events\\\": [');\nif (start === -1) { console.log('No events array found'); return; }\nconst eventsStr = content.substring(start + 10); // skip 'events\\\": ['\nconst trimmed = eventsStr.trim();\n\n// Remove trailing comma and close bracket\nlet clean = trimmed;\nif (clean.endsWith(',]') || clean.endsWith(']')) {\n  clean = clean.replace(/,\\s*\\]\\s*$/, ']');\n}\n\ntry {\n  const events = JSON.parse(clean);\n  console.log('Events count:', events.length);\n\n  // Count event types\n  const typeCount = {};\n  for (const e of events) {\n    typeCount[e.type] = (typeCount[e.type] || 0) + 1;\n  }\n  const sorted = Object.entries(typeCount).sort((a, b) => b[1] - a[1]);\n  for (const [type, count] of sorted.slice(0, 30)) {\n    console.log('type', type, ':', count);\n  }\n} catch(e) {\n  console.log('Parse error:', e.message.substring(0, 100));\n  console.log('Last 100 chars:', clean.slice(-100));\n}\n\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":1899,"output":545,"cacheRead":114560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":117004,"cost":{"input":0.00026586000000000003,"output":0.00015260000000000002,"cacheRead":0.00320768,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00362614}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779257334491,"responseId":"530d5a08-ff88-4253-a64a-aaad6346e863"}}
