{"type":"message","id":"0d0f35d9","parentId":"ee1f604e","timestamp":"2026-05-20T06:09:57.620Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, the issue is that the last line `{\"params\":{\"address_list\":[\"216.239.34.223:443\"],\"aliases\":[]` is NOT complete! It doesn't have a closing `}}`. Chrome probably crashed or was killed before it finished writing the netlog.\n\nThis means the netlog is incomplete. But I can still parse the events up to the last complete event. Let me parse the events array line by line and extract only valid events.\n\nActually, a better approach: since the file is line-oriented (each event is on its own line with trailing comma), I can:\n1. Read all lines from the events array\n2. Parse each line individually\n3. Skip invalid lines\n\nLet me write a proper parser.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_cYRReEuOFNrnneR3nWEe5486","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace; node -e \"\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst content = fs.readFileSync('chrome_netlog.json', 'utf8');\nconst lines = content.split('\\n');\n\n// Find the start of events array\nlet inEvents = false;\nlet cookieFound = false;\nlet lineNum = 0;\n\nfor (const rawLine of lines) {\n  lineNum++;\n  const line = rawLine.trim();\n  \n  if (line.includes('\\\"events\\\"')) {\n    inEvents = true;\n    continue;\n  }\n  if (!inEvents) continue;\n  if (line === '[' || line === '') continue;\n  if (line === ']' || line === ']}') break;\n  \n  // Clean: remove trailing comma\n  const clean = line.replace(/,$/, '');\n  if (clean.length < 10) continue;\n  \n  try {\n    const e = JSON.parse(clean);\n    // Look for HTTP request headers with cookies\n    if (e.type === 149 && e.params && e.params.headers) {\n      const h = e.params.headers;\n      const cookie = h.Cookie || h.cookie || '';\n      const url = e.params.url || '';\n      if (cookie && (url.includes('tapd') || cookie.includes('tapd'))) {\n        console.log('COOKIE HEADER in', url.substring(0, 80));\n        // Extract individual cookies\n        cookie.split(';').forEach(pair => {\n          const parts = pair.trim().split('=');\n          if (parts.length >= 2 && parts[0].trim().startsWith('tapd')) {\n            console.log('  ' + parts[0].trim() + '=' + parts.slice(1).join('=').substring(0, 40));\n          }\n        });\n        cookieFound = true;\n      }\n    }\n  } catch(e) {\n    // Skip invalid events\n    if (lineNum > lines.length - 5) {\n      console.log('Last line invalid:', line.substring(0, 50));\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nif (!cookieFound) {\n  console.log('No TAPD cookie in HTTP headers found');\n}\n\" 2>&1","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":293,"output":687,"cacheRead":121472,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":122452,"cost":{"input":0.000041020000000000004,"output":0.00019236,"cacheRead":0.003401216,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003634596}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779257390291,"responseId":"5a080779-f2e3-4da5-8340-f71a0cd246b8"}}
