{"type":"message","id":"0da55fc6","parentId":"2e37891d","timestamp":"2026-05-20T06:10:07.565Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Actually, I just realized something important. Chrome might redirect to the login page immediately, and the tapdsession cookie might not be sent in the `Cookie` header because the TAPD server might set the cookie after a successful login, not before. Chrome's netlog will show what was sent in HTTP headers.\n\nIf the first request to TAPD already has the tapdsession cookie (because Chrome loaded it from the cookie store), then the Cookie header in the HTTP request should include it.\n\nBut there's another consideration: Chrome might use the cookie store directly without sending the `Cookie` header through the netlog. Or the `Cookie` header might be stripped from the log even with `IncludeSensitive` mode.\n\nLet me run the scan and see.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_fmg6P6bsIjx3v5InnIe07469","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace; node scripts/scan_netlog.mjs","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":44,"output":240,"cacheRead":123264,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":123548,"cost":{"input":0.00000616,"output":0.00006720000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0034513919999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003524752}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779257403648,"responseId":"16893b23-4991-4652-95c2-b5848bbb9714"}}
{"type":"message","id":"90956e16","parentId":"0da55fc6","timestamp":"2026-05-20T06:10:07.846Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_fmg6P6bsIjx3v5InnIe07469","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Scanning 22110 lines...\nNo TAPD cookie in HTTP headers found in netlog\nThe request might have been redirected before cookies were sent"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":261,"aggregated":"Scanning 22110 lines...\nNo TAPD cookie in HTTP headers found in netlog\nThe request might have been redirected before cookies were sent","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779257407846}}
{"type":"message","id":"0807f216","parentId":"90956e16","timestamp":"2026-05-20T06:10:15.186Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The netlog doesn't contain any TAPD HTTP request with Cookie headers. This means either:\n1. Chrome TAPD request was blocked/redirected before any cookies were sent\n2. The netlog entry didn't include the cookie values (stripped for privacy)\n3. Chrome went to `https://www.tapd.cn/` which redirected to `cloud_logins/login` without sending cookies\n\nActually, option 3 is most likely. The tapdsession is tied to a specific subdomain (e.g., `*.tapd.cn`). If Chrome navigates to `https://www.tapd.cn/` and the server redirects to a login page BEFORE Chrome sends cookies, then the cookies won't appear in the netlog.\n\nBut actually, Chrome should send cookies with EVERY request to tapd.cn, including the first one. The Cookie header should include `tapdsession=...` in the request.\n\nLet me check the netlog for ALL requests to tapd.cn, not just those with type=149.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_UGHVTuqV76ze7iDybo8W6041","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import fs from 'fs';\n\nconst NETLOG = 'C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\chrome_netlog.json';\nconst content = fs.readFileSync(NETLOG, 'utf8');\nconst lines = content.split('\\n');\n\nconsole.log(`Scanning ${lines.length} lines for any tapd.cn reference...`);\n\n// First, count tapd references\nlet tapdRefCount = 0;\nfor (const rawLine of lines) {\n  if (rawLine.includes('tapd')) {\n    tapdRefCount++;\n    if (tapdRefCount <= 5) {\n      console.log(rawLine.substring(0, 200));\n    }\n  }\n}\nconsole.log(`\\nTotal tapd references: ${tapdRefCount}`);\n\n// If no tapd references, check what URLs were actually accessed\nif (tapdRefCount === 0) {\n  console.log('\\nChrome may have failed to navigate to TAPD. Checking URL events...');\n  let urlCount = 0;\n  for (const rawLine of lines) {\n    const line = rawLine.trim().replace(/,$/, '');\n    if (line.includes('\"url\"') && !line.includes('constants')) {\n      try {\n        const e = JSON.parse(line);\n        if (e.params && e.params.url) {\n          urlCount++;\n          if (urlCount <= 10) {\n            console.log(`  ${e.params.url.substring(0, 100)}`);\n          }\n        }\n      } catch {}\n    }\n  }\n  console.log(`\\nTotal URL events: ${urlCount}`);\n}\n","path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\scan_tapd.mjs"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":70,"output":637,"cacheRead":123520,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":124227,"cost":{"input":0.000009800000000000001,"output":0.00017836000000000002,"cacheRead":0.00345856,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00364672}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779257407849,"responseId":"cc4081af-fe72-4942-a186-dd3e9eed34ea"}}
