{"type":"message","id":"f46e49ed","parentId":"7356f3db","timestamp":"2026-05-20T06:37:15.183Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"HFS is running. The password is stored as SRP verifier which can't be reversed. Let me check if the old-hfs.exe has a different config or if I can look at the config more carefully.\n\nActually, wait. Let me check the `accounts` section of the config more carefully. In HFS v3, when you first set up, it creates the SRP verifier from the password. But maybe there's also a plaintext password stored somewhere, or maybe the user set a simple password that I can guess.\n\nActually, the best approach is to check common passwords or ask the user if they have a hint. But let me first check if there's a `--password` argument in the command line.\n\nLet me also look at the old-hfs.exe - maybe its config format is different and stores plaintext passwords.\n\nActually, wait. Let me check if there are any other config files or backup files in the directory that might contain the password in a different format.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_3FC3O1ohEJZEGdaxbB0c2109","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Content \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\Downloads\\hfs\\config.yaml\" -Encoding UTF8 | Select-Object -First 20"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":116,"output":276,"cacheRead":155392,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":155784,"cost":{"input":0.00001624,"output":0.00007728,"cacheRead":0.0043509759999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.004444495999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779259030788,"responseId":"150acc22-2ab7-402b-8a91-f0679c586015"}}
