{"type":"message","id":"b6be3ddf","parentId":"093c9779","timestamp":"2026-05-20T06:37:20.858Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"HFS v3 uses SRP (Secure Remote Password) which means the password is NOT stored in plaintext. The `srp` field is a cryptographic verifier that can't be reversed to get the original password.\n\nHowever, there's a trick. I can modify the config.yaml to remove the password or change it. Or I could use the HFS command-line interface to reset the password.\n\nHFS v3 has a command-line interface that allows:\n- `passwd <username>` - change password for a user\n- Or editing the config directly\n\nLet me try using HFS's built-in CLI to change the password. Or, even simpler, I can edit the config to remove the SRP field, which would effectively remove the password requirement.\n\nActually, let me try a different approach. HFS v3 has a TUI (terminal user interface). I can run `hfs.exe --cli` to access the command line, and then use `passwd admin` to set a new password. Or I can just modify the config.\n\nLet me just tell the user that HFS v3 uses SRP and the password can't be recovered, but I can reset it.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"主人，HFS v3 用的是 SRP 加密存储密码，原始的密码没法从配置里解出来。\n\n不过我可以直接帮你重置密码。要现在重置吗？我改一下 `config.yaml` 清掉密码，或者设个新密码～"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":399,"output":297,"cacheRead":155776,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":156472,"cost":{"input":0.000055860000000000004,"output":0.00008316000000000001,"cacheRead":0.004361728,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.004500748}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779259035453,"responseId":"73add2a4-259e-4f2e-8a55-83bb5792571e"}}
