{"type":"message","id":"69f0c35c","parentId":"a2d22ca8","timestamp":"2026-05-20T06:56:58.519Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me try to compute the SRP verifier for \"111111\". \n\nHFS v3 on GitHub uses a specific SRP implementation. Let me check the HFS source code or npm package to understand how it generates the SRP verifier.\n\nActually, I just realized - HFS v3 is built with Node.js and the SRP is computed in JavaScript. I can write a script that runs HFS's own password hashing to generate the correct SRP verifier.\n\nBut I don't have access to HFS's source code easily. Let me try a different approach - I'll use the HFS HTTP API to change the password.\n\nActually, since HFS is running on port 80, I can send HTTP requests to it. The admin API might allow password changes through authenticated requests.\n\nWait, but I can't authenticate because I don't know the password...\n\nLet me try the brute-force approach: delete the accounts section from config.yaml, restart HFS without auth, then set the password via the web UI.\n\nActually, a better approach: let me just compute the SRP verifier for \"111111\" using the same algorithm HFS uses. HFS v3 is open source on GitHub. Let me check the source.\n\nHFS v3 uses the `srp` npm package. The formula for the verifier is:\nverifier = g^x mod N\nwhere x = SHA256(salt || SHA256(I || \":\" || P))\n- I = username (e.g., \"admin\")\n- P = password (e.g., \"111111\")\n- salt = random bytes\n- N = a large safe prime (from RFC 5054)\n- g = a generator (usually 2)\n\nThe specific N and g are from RFC 5054 for 2048-bit SRP. Let me write a Node.js script to generate the SRP verifier.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_54E05EakpDNPli4SG4RU9747","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"/**\n * 计算 HFS v3 使用的 SRP 密码验证器\n * HFS 使用 srp 包 (srp-js) 的 2048-bit 参数\n */\nimport crypto from 'crypto';\n\n// RFC 5054 2048-bit prime (N) for SRP\nconst N_HEX = '';\n\nconsole.log('This approach requires the srp package...');\nconsole.log('Let me try a different method.');\n\n// Actually, let me try using hfs's own binary. \n// We can run hfs in a way that accepts the password change.\n// Or we can just remove the password from config and restart.\n\nconsole.log('\\n=== Alternative: Remove password protection ===');\nconsole.log('Delete the accounts section from config.yaml');\nconsole.log('Then restart HFS and set password via web UI');\n","path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\compute_hfs_srp.mjs"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":104,"output":1187,"cacheRead":158336,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":159627,"cost":{"input":0.000014560000000000001,"output":0.00033236,"cacheRead":0.004433408,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0047803279999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779260202651,"responseId":"2bb07b9d-5b93-459b-bc3e-4d8316f8e5a0"}}
