{"type":"message","id":"7890dd17","parentId":"3fd34898","timestamp":"2026-05-20T06:57:20.624Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, `srp-js` installed. Now let me check what HFS v3 uses for SRP parameters and generate the verifier for \"111111\".\n\nHFS v3 uses the `srp` package which uses specific parameters. Let me check what's in the HFS config's SRP string format. The format is \"verifier|salt\" where both are decimal numbers.\n\nActually, let me check the HFS source code on GitHub to understand the exact SRP computation. But that might take too long. Let me try a different approach.\n\nActually, the simplest approach by far: just use `hfs.exe` itself to set the password. I can pipe the password change commands through stdin. Let me try:\n\n```\necho \"passwd admin 111111\" | hfs.exe --cli save\n```\n\nOr I can use the HFS web API. Since HFS is running and I can access it locally (potentially without password if I remove the account), I can make API calls.\n\nActually wait, let me try the simplest thing first: remove the `accounts` block from config.yaml, restart HFS, access the admin page without password, set the password there.\n\nOr even simpler: write a Node.js script that generates the SRP verifier using the same parameters HFS uses.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_lMzi8KVzEHJgMBOzVJZF5731","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace; node -e \"\nimport srp from 'srp-js';\n\n// HFS v3 uses 2048-bit SRP group from RFC 5054\n// The prime (N) and generator (g) are standard for 2048b\nconst params = srp.params[4096] || srp.params[2048];\nconsole.log('Available params:', Object.keys(srp.params || {}));\n\n// Try to compute the verifier for admin:111111\nconst username = 'admin';\nconst password = '111111';\nconst salt = crypto.randomBytes(16);\n\n// SRP verifier = g^x mod N where x = SHA256(salt | SHA256(username:password))\nconst identity = Buffer.from(username + ':' + password);\nconst innerHash = crypto.createHash('sha256').update(identity).digest();\nconst xBuf = crypto.createHash('sha256').update(Buffer.concat([salt, innerHash])).digest();\nconst x = BigInt('0x' + xBuf.toString('hex'));\n\n// v = g^x mod N\n// For 2048-bit SRP from RFC 5054\nconst N_2048 = BigInt('0x' + '');\nconst G = 2n;\nconst v = (G ** x) % N_2048;\n\nconsole.log('Verifier:', v.toString());\nconsole.log('Salt (hex):', salt.toString('hex'));\n\" 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":52,"output":1188,"cacheRead":160000,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":161240,"cost":{"input":0.000007280000000000001,"output":0.00033264000000000004,"cacheRead":0.00448,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00481992}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779260227298,"responseId":"21c832ff-fcd3-4667-b444-6d6638fb3940"}}
