{"type":"message","id":"d6052c17","parentId":"979efe2d","timestamp":"2026-05-20T07:29:18.370Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see! There are multiple HFS instances running:\n1. One started at 14:58:37 (the one I started with Start-Process)\n2. Another started at 14:59:54 (maybe from the first CLI attempt)\n\nAnd the logs show \"http port 80 busy: hfs.exe\" - this means port 80 is already taken. The second instance tried to use port 8000 instead but that's also busy.\n\nBut the key issue might be simpler. Let me check: when I changed the config to remove the password, the HFS might have been configured with different settings. Let me check:\n\n1. What port is HFS actually serving on?\n2. Can I make a request to it?\n3. Is the VFS path correct?\n\nActually, looking at the config again, I only changed the `config.yaml`. The old config had VFS pointing to `D:\\cdn_solo\\`. But there was also a running HFS instance before my changes that might have a different config in memory.\n\nWait - the original HFS process (PID 35000) was running with the old config before I killed it. Then I modified config.yaml and started HFS again. The new HFS instance should be using the new config.\n\nBut there are now 2 HFS instances running. Let me kill both and restart fresh. But first, let me check what the actual HFS serving looks like.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_nxhuyyM4m996PhuWFLHO7964","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查 HFS 在监听什么端口\nnetstat -ano | findstr \"hfs\" 2>&1; Write-Host \"---\"; # 检查 cdn_solo 里 Version 目录\nGet-ChildItem \"D:\\cdn_solo\\Version\" -Name | Select-Object -First 10; Write-Host \"---\"; Get-ChildItem \"D:\\cdn_solo\" -Depth 1 -Name | Select-Object -First 30","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":275,"output":454,"cacheRead":169600,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":170329,"cost":{"input":0.0000385,"out