{"type":"message","id":"8fd49690","parentId":"fae98c50","timestamp":"2026-05-20T07:29:52.038Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting findings:\n- `http://127.0.0.1:8000/` → 200 (HFS is running on port 8000)\n- `http://127.0.0.1:8000/Version/version_20260312.bytes` → 404 (can't find the file)\n- `http://127.0.0.1/` → 000 (port 80 not responding, timeout)\n\nSo the problem is:\n1. HFS is on port **8000** now, not 80 (the original was probably on 80)\n2. Files return **404** - the VFS path might not be mapped correctly\n\nThe 404 for the file suggests the VFS mapping issue. When I removed the `accounts` section from config.yaml, the `vfs` section was kept intact. But maybe the original HFS that was running had additional settings in its in-memory config.\n\nWait, let me check the current config.yaml vs what was originally there.\n\nActually, looking at the HFS VFS structure, the root directory maps to `D:\\cdn_solo\\`. So requesting `/Version/version_20260312.bytes` should map to `D:\\cdn_solo\\Version\\version_20260312.bytes`. Let me verify this file exists.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_8W8Q18zDHDtQuUkcXVHV6688","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Test-Path \"D:\\cdn_solo\\Version\\version_20260312.bytes\"; Write-Host \"---\"; # 检查 VFS 完整路径\nGet-ChildItem \"D:\\cdn_solo\" | Select-Object Name, Mode | Format-Table; Write-Host \"=== ROOT ===\"; # 试 HFS 根目录\ncurl.exe -s http://127.0.0.1:8000/ 2>&1 | Select-Object -First 20","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":94,"output":439,"cacheRead":172416,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":172949,"cost":{"input":0.000013160000000000001,"output":0.00012292,"cacheRead":0.0048276479999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.004963728}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779262185332,"responseId":"b5f4f1ce-d588-41be-9b75-4b269a5217f2"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ec1f408f","parentId":"8fd49690","timestamp":"2026-05-20T07:29:52.730Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_8W8Q18zDHDtQuUkcXVHV6688","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"True\r\n---\n\r\nName      Mode  \r\n----      ----  \r\nLog       d-----\r\nTemp      d-----\r\nupdate    d-----\r\nVersion   d-----\r\nREADME.md -a----\r\n\r\n\r\n=== ROOT ===\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width\" /><style>body { font-size: 16pt; }</style><title>File server</title><body><a href='/?get=login'>Login</a>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href='cdn_solo/'>cdn_solo/</a>\r\n</ul>"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":682,"aggregated":"True\r\n---\n\r\nName      Mode  \r\n----      ----  \r\nLog       d-----\r\nTemp      d-----\r\nupdate    d-----\r\nVersion   d-----\r\nREADME.md -a----\r\n\r\n\r\n=== ROOT ===\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width\" /><style>body { font-size: 16pt; }</style><title>File server</title><body><a href='/?get=login'>Login</a>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href='cdn_solo/'>cdn_solo/</a>\r\n</ul>","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779262192730}}
{"type":"message","id":"8f5a03ff","parentId":"ec1f408f","timestamp":"2026-05-20T07:30:00.696Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found the issue! The HFS root page shows:\n```\n<li><a href='cdn_solo/'>cdn_solo/</a>\n```\n\nThe VFS is serving `cdn_solo/` as a SUBFOLDER of the root. So the path would be `http://127.0.0.1:8000/cdn_solo/Version/version_20260312.bytes`, not just `http://127.0.0.1:8000/Version/...`.\n\nWait, but the original config had:\n```yaml\nvfs:\n  children:\n    - name: cdn_solo\n      source: D:\\cdn_solo\\\n```\n\nSo indeed `cdn_solo` is a child node under the root. But the original HFS that was working probably had a different VFS structure that served files directly at root level.\n\nBut wait, also:\n1. The original HFS was on port 80, now it's on port 8000\n2. The VFS mapping has `cdn_solo` as a subfolder, not the root\n3. There are multiple HFS instances\n\nI think the main issues are:\n1. **Multiple HFS instances** - process 32904 tried port 80 but failed (busy), process 15724 is on port 8000\n2. **Port changed** - if the user was accessing port 80, they'd get nothing (port 80 is now serving something else or nothing)\n3. **VFS structure** - files are under `/cdn_solo/` path, not root\n\nLet me check what was on port 80 originally:","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"找到原因了！"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_m5rpDqCPcEC35ucGj2S10271","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 看看 80 端口到底谁占着\nnetstat -ano | Select-String \":80 \" | Select-String \"LISTEN\" 2>&1; Write-Host \"=== Process ===\"; Get-Process -Id 32904 | Select-Object Id, StartTime; Get-Process -Id 15724 | Select-Object Id, StartTime","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":166,"output":480,"cacheRead":172928,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":173574,"cost":{"input":0.00002324,"output":0.00013440000000000001,"cacheRead":0.004841984,"cacheWrite":0,"total":