{"type":"message","id":"bcd3b12c","parentId":"a55c60f1","timestamp":"2026-05-20T07:30:32.022Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, no port 80 listener now. Let me also put the config back with a password (since the user asked to set it to 111111) or keep it without password and let them set it.\n\nActually, the user hasn't confirmed they set the password yet. Let me just start HFS without password and let them set it later. But more importantly, let me fix the config to NOT have cdn_solo as a subfolder, but serve directly from root, AND keep the original VFS structure.\n\nWait, actually, looking at the original config:\n```yaml\nvfs:\n  children:\n    - name: cdn_solo\n      source: D:\\cdn_solo\\\n```\n\nThis means `cdn_solo` was always a subfolder of the root. The original HFS served files at `http://IP/cdn_solo/Version/xx.bytes`. This was the original configuration.\n\nSo the main issue was just the port changing from 80 to 8000. The VFS path was always `/cdn_solo/...`.\n\nLet me start HFS cleanly on port 80 now.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_O0fXqMw3fRV9JnkndlBp3352","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"version: 3.1.5\nplatform: win32-x64\nvfs:\n  children:\n    - name: cdn_solo\n      source: D:\\cdn_solo\\\n","path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\Downloads\\hfs\\config.yaml"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":82,"output":344,"cacheRead":174976,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":175402,"cost":{"input":0.00001148,"output":0.00009632000000000001,"cacheRead":0.004899328,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005007128}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779262225979,"responseId":"94ab745a-58c5-474d-9aca-9447da6e5fa8"}}
