{"type":"message","id":"38a3c68e","parentId":"bd28823b","timestamp":"2026-05-20T08:42:33.477Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants the hyperlinks to use the Chinese description text as the link text, instead of showing the raw URL. Since this is in a Feishu chat, I need to use Feishu's link format.\n\nIn Feishu, the way to create hyperlinks depends on the message type:\n- For `text` messages: Feishu doesn't natively support clickable text links in plain text messages\n- For `post` (rich text) messages: supports `[text](url)` format\n\nActually, in Feishu's text message format, URLs are automatically detected and made clickable. But for custom link text, I need to use the `post` (rich text) message format.\n\nHowever, since I'm responding in this session and my replies go to Feishu, I'm not sure what format my messages are sent in. Let me check - the TOOLS.md mentioned using `node scripts/feishu_send_group.mjs` for group messages with `<at>` tags. \n\nFor a direct message, OpenClaw automatically routes my reply to Feishu. The format depends on the channel configuration.\n\nIn Feishu, markdown links `[text](url)` are NOT natively supported in text messages. But for rich text (post) messages, you can use the post format.\n\nActually, the simplest approach in Feishu is to just format the commit messages with the TAPD links embedded naturally. Since Feishu auto-detects URLs and makes them clickable, I can structure the message like:\n\n```\n【小狗头人】小狗头人历险记... (https://www.tapd.cn/31253609/s/1490269)\n```\n\nBut the user wants the Chinese description to be the hyperlink. In Feishu text messages, this isn't directly possible. I'd need to use the post (rich text) API.\n\nHowever, OpenClaw's Feishu integration might support markdown in certain message types. Let me just try using markdown link format and see if it works. If Feishu doesn't support it, I'll adjust.\n\nActually, looking at the Feishu send script (`feishu_send_group.mjs`), it uses `msg_type: 'text'` which doesn't support rich links. For rich text, I'd need to use `msg_type: 'post'` with the post content format.\n\nBut since I'm replying in this session (not using the send script), OpenClaw handles the message routing. Let me just send the content with markdown-style links and see how it renders.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_wIMjRzSovcu8Zaptt6Fd8080","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\"; git log --since=\"7 days ago\" --author=\"yezhijun\" --author=\"ZTGAME\\\\yyzypublic\" --format=\"%s\" --reverse 2>&1","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":34459,"output":653,"cacheRead":163840,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":198952,"cost":{"input":0.00482426,"output":0.00018284,"cacheRead":0.0045875199999999994,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00959462}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779266543147,"responseId":"9b3d84bf-85c9-422d-8fcf-f6fcd7ae2945"}}
