{"type":"compaction","id":"2f6d10c3","parentId":"a6d7ec96","timestamp":"2026-05-20T09:09:12.045Z","summary":"## Goal\n1. Configure colleague private chat restrictions (non-whitelisted colleagues redirect to group @)\n2. Open 周以天's private chat permissions\n3. Optimize line breaks in bug submission feedback messages\n4. Switch to DeepSeek model\n5. Extract 周以天's TAPD cookies from Chrome → save to workspace for bug submission\n6. Manage dual TAPD accounts (叶枝君 + 周以天) with daily keepalive\n7. Set bug submissions to use 周以天's TAPD account by default\n8. Fix HFS (HTTP File Server) password and availability issues\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- DeepSeek model should be default (set at end of conversation: `deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash`)\n- Bug submissions: use 周以天's TAPD account exclusively\n- Both TAPD accounts need daily keepalive\n- Non-whitelisted colleagues messaging privately → redirect to group @\n- 周以天 (`ou_348eeddd81d4c03865f9f1684fce6966`) has private chat permission\n- Feishu messages: use real newlines, never literal `\\n`\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Updated `COLLEAGUE_WHITELIST.md`: other colleagues private chat → redirect to group @\n- [x] Added 周以天 to private chat whitelist with full access\n- [x] Updated `MEMORY.md` with private chat restriction rules\n- [x] Switched model to `deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash`\n- [x] Extracted 周以天's TAPD cookies via Cookie Editor export → saved to `tapd_cookies.json` (14 cookies, verified working)\n- [x] Extracted 叶枝君's TAPD cookies via Cookie Editor export → saved to `tapd_cookies_yezhijun.json` (17 cookies)\n- [x] Backup: `tapd_cookies_zhouyitian.json` = 周以天's cookies\n- [x] Rewrote `scripts/tapd_keepalive.mjs` to support dual accounts (`node scripts/tapd_keepalive.mjs` = 周以天, `node scripts/tapd_keepalive.mjs yezhijun` = 叶枝君)\n- [x] Updated `HEARTBEAT.md` with dual-account keepalive config\n- [x] Updated `MEMORY.md` with dual-account TAPD info\n- [x] Tested keepalive for both accounts — both succeed, tapdsession renewed to 2026-05-27\n- [x] Submitted test bug to 周以天: https://www.tapd.cn/tapd_fe/31253609/bug/detail/1131253609001016563\n- [x] HFS password cleared (SRP format — unrecoverable), HFS restarted on port 80 successfully\n- [x] HFS issue diagnosed: multiple instances conflicting on ports, resolved by killing all and restarting clean\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] User asked to set default model to DeepSeek (done for this session, but should persist in MEMORY.md)\n\n### Blocked\n- Chrome 148 App Bound Encryption prevents automated cookie extraction — Cookie Editor manual export is the required workaround\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Cookie file structure**: `tapd_cookies.json` = 周以天 (main/default), `tapd_cookies_zhouyitian.json` = 周以天 backup, `tapd_cookies_yezhijun.json` = 叶枝君\n- **Cookie extraction method**: Chrome 148 uses App Bound Encryption; manual Cookie Editor export is the only reliable method\n- **HFS password reset**: SRP verifier in config.yaml is not reversible; cleared accounts section, user must set password via web UI at `http://192.168.95.85/~/admin/`\n- **Bug submission account**: Always use 周以天 (`tapd_cookies.json`)\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Persist default model preference (`deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash`) in MEMORY.md\n2. Confirm with user if HFS password was set to 111111 via web UI\n3. Daily: run `node scripts/tapd_keepalive.mjs` and `node scripts/tapd_keepalive.mjs yezhijun` (HEARTBEAT handles this)\n4. When TAPD cookies expire (~2026-05-27): ask user to re-export via Cookie Editor\n\n## Critical Context\n- **TAPD cookie files**:\n  - `C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\tapd_cookies.json` — 周以天, 14 cookies, tapdsession expires 2026-05-27\n  - `C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\tapd_cookies_yezhijun.json` — 叶枝君, 17 cookies\n  - `C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\tapd_cookies_zhouyitian.json` — 周以天 backup\n- **TAPD keepalive script**: `node scripts/tapd_keepalive.mjs [zhouyitian|yezhijun]`\n- **HFS**: Running on port 80, PID 35308, serving `D:\\cdn_solo\\` at `/cdn_solo/` path; no password currently set; admin UI: `http://192.168.95.85/~/admin/`\n- **周以天 Feishu ID**: `ou_348eeddd81d4c03865f9f1684fce6966`\n- **叶枝君 Feishu ID**: `ou_6509d346e8d50ef882f89c436e6c977f`\n- **Default model**: `deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash` (session-set; may need MEMORY.md update)\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nThe user (Yousan/叶枝君) asked to set DeepSeek as the default model in OpenClaw.\n\n## Early Progress\n- Assistant agreed to switch the default model to DeepSeek\n- Examined `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` to understand config structure\n- Used `openclaw config get` to explore config paths:\n  - `defaultModel` → path not found\n  - `gateway` → found port/auth/mode settings, no model config there\n  - `agent` → path not found\n  - `models` → **found the models config**, which includes providers:\n    - `openai-proxy` (Claude Sonnet 4.6, Claude Opus 4.7)\n    - `qwen` (qwen3.5-plus, qwen3-max, etc.)\n    - Other providers visible in truncated output (modelstudio with MiniMax, GLM, Kimi, etc.)\n- Current default appears to be `openai-proxy/giant-claude-sonnet-4-6` (from session_status)\n- The `openclaw config patch` and `openclaw config set` commands are available for making changes\n\n## Context for Suffix\n- The assistant is still investigating how to set a default model — no DeepSeek provider/model has been found yet in the config\n- The `models` config uses a `mode: merge` structure with named providers, each containing a `models` array\n- DeepSeek may need to be added as a new provider or located in the existing config (possibly in the truncated portion)\n- The next step likely involves finding DeepSeek in the models list and identifying the correct config path to set it as default\n\n<read-files>\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\plugin-skills\\tapd-bug-create\\SKILL.md\nC:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\feishu_send_group.mjs\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\nC:\\Users\